LAYOUT.GUIDANCE_L1_2:
With these butons you can navigate in the Layout editor.
Hand symbol ("move view"):
Click this button to zoom in and out with your mousewheel or to move the view to left, right, up and down.
Short cut: Keep "Alt" pushed on your keyboard to jump into the "move view" mode.
Release "Alt" to get back to the "selection mode".
Finger symbol ("selection mode"):
Click this button to select elements from your layout.
Keep "Shift" pushed on your keyboard to multiselect elements. By selecting elements, you can change their properties.
Plus symbol ("add mode"):
Click this sybol to add new elements. Once this mode is selected, you will stay in this mode, until pushing the big "Enter" key on your keyboard. This will bring you back into the selection mode.
LAYOUT.GUIDANCE_L2_2:
With these elements you can draw and describe your missions.
1. Background: You can either load abackground layout as a picture or select "No Background image" on the bottom
2. Reference line: In order to understand the dimensions of the layout, please draw a reference line and scale it in the menu window on the right side.
After you've done this, never change the reference in this project.
3. Add Sources, Destinations or points where both is done (Source & Destinations. Follow the instructions of the pop-ups.
4. In case of a tugger train application, also set your stop points for your routes
5. Only now start drawing your paths. Start drawing without curves, but make sure the ends are connected (blue dot).
To create curves or intersections, keep pushing "Shift" on your keyboard and multiselect to pathes.
Then click the appearing circle and choose to draw a curve with or without keeping the original path.
LAYOUT.GUIDANCE_L3_2:
Here you can switch between the view of missions or created layout elements.
In each of the tabs, you can edit missions or layout elements and adjust their properties.
